article.headline: Saint Mary's 73, New Mexico St. 53
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- Mitchell Young scored 20 points to lead St. Mary's (Calif.) to a 73-53 victory over New Mexico State on Thursday night. Matthew Dellavedova had 12 points and six assists and Stephen Holt scored 10 points for the Gaels (10-2). Christian Kabongo scored 16 points and Hernst Laroche added 12 for the Aggies (6-8). St. Mary's led 48-41 with 13:07 remaining and took control with a 13-4 run highlighted by consecutive 3-pointers by Mickey McConnell, Dellavedova and Holt. The Gaels converted 15 turnovers into 22 points and outscored New Mexico State 34-8 in the paint.
